ments start taking reservations\n|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/stlouis/news/2011/04/13/laurel-apartments-start-taking.html\n|accessdate=June 22, 2011\n|newspaper=St. Louis Business Journal\n|location=St. Louis, Missouri\n|date=April 13, 2011\n}}\n*{{cite news\n|last=Volkmann\n|first=Kelsey\n|title=Touring Peabody Opera House renovation\n|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/stlouis/blog/2011/05/touring-peabody-opera-house-renovation.html\n|accessdate=June 22, 2011\n|newspaper=St. Louis Business Journal\n|location=St. Louis, Missouri\n|date=May 17, 2011\n}}\n*{{Cite web\n| last = Zimmer\n| first = Keith B.\n| title = Casualty List of Soldiers From St. Louis Who Died During World War II\n| publisher = St. Louis Public Library\n| date = February 2000\n| url = http://www.slpl.lib.mo.us/libsrc/obww11a.htm\n| accessdate = June 22, 2011\n| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110905231158/http://www.slpl.lib.mo.us/libsrc/obww11a.htm\n| archive-date = September 5, 2011\n| url-status = dead\n}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{refbegin|colwidth=30em}}\n* Anderson, Galusha. ''The Story of a Border City During the Civil War'' (1908) [https://books.google.com/books?hl=en&lr=&id=42UuAAAAYAAJ online].\n* Cowan, Aaron. ''A Nice Place to Visit: Tourism and Urban Revitalization in the Postwar Rustbelt'' (2016) compares Cincinnati, St. Louis, Pittsburgh, and Baltimore in the wake of deindustrialization.\n* {{Cite book\n| last = Gerteis\n| first = Louis S.\n| authorlink = \n| title = Civil War St. Louis\n| publisher = University Press of Kansas\n| series =\n| volume =\n| edition =\n| year = 2001\n| location = Lawrence, Kansas\n| isbn = 978-0-7006-1124-9\n| url =\n}}\n* {{cite book\n| last       = Graff\n| first      = Daniel A.\n| editor-last  = Morris Spencer\n| editor-first = Thomas\n| title         = The Other Missouri History: Populists, Prostitutes, and Regular Folk\n| chapter-url           = https://books.google.com/books?id=fp7TAyM7cTwC\n| year      = 2004\n| publisher 