| Ship armament = *1 \u00d7 [[Oto Melara 76 mm|{{cvt|76|mm}}/62 caliber Oto Melara gun]] (A position)\n*1 \u00d7 [[Rheinmetall Oerlikon Millennium Gun|{{cvt|35|mm}} Oerlikon Millennium gun]] (Y position)\n*2 \u00d7 {{cvt|12.7|mm}} guns (B position)\n| Ship armour = \n| Ship armor = \n| Ship aircraft = 1 \u00d7 [[Bell 212|AB212]], [[Bell 412|AB412]], or [[Eurocopter AS565 Panther|AS565]]\n| Ship aircraft facilities = Landing pad<ref name=\"Navantia Avante 1400 patrol ship\">{{cite web|title=Navantia Avante 1400 patrol ship|url=http://www.navantia.es/ckfinder/userfiles/files/BVL(1).pdf|publisher=Navantia|accessdate=13 July 2013}}</ref>\n| Ship notes = \n}}\n|}\n\n'''''Naiguat\u00e1'' (GC-23)''', was a {{convert|79.9|m|adj=on}} littoral [[patrol boat]] of the Venezuelan Coast Guard.  The vessel was constructed by [[Navantia]] in [[C\u00e1diz]], Spain beginning in 2008. On 30 March 2020, the vessel rammed the [[cruise ship]] {{ship||RCGS Resolute}} in international waters and sank. \n\n==Construction and career==\n''Naiguat\u00e1'' was the third ship of the {{sclass-|Guaicamacuto|patrol boat|0}} BVLs.  BVL stands for \"Buque de Vigilancia de Litoral,\" which is Spanish for littoral [[Patrol boat|surveillance ship]].  It had a [[Displacement (ship)|displacement]] of 1,720 tons.<ref>{{cite news |last1= Lagneau |first=Laurent |title=Un patrouilleur de la marine v\u00e9n\u00e9zu\u00e9lienne a coul\u00e9 apr\u00e8s avoir percut\u00e9 un navire de croisi\u00e8re |url=http://www.opex360.com/2020/04/02/un-patrouilleur-de-la-marine-venezuelienne-a-coule-apres-avoir-percute-un-navire-de-croisiere/ |access-date=4 April 2020 |work=opex360 |date=2 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404093306/http://www.opex360.com/2020/04/02/un-patrouilleur-de-la-marine-venezuelienne-a-coule-apres-avoir-percute-un-navire-de-croisiere/ |archive-date=4 April 2020 |language=fr |quote=affichant 1.720 tonnes}}</ref>  It was built by Navantia in Spain at the [[San Fernando, C\u00e1diz|San Fernando]] shipyards in C\u00e1diz,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gonz\u00e1lez |first1=Miguel |title=Espa\u00f1a retira su apoyo al buque de guerra 'Comandante Eterno Hugo Ch\u00e1vez' |url=https://elpais.com/internacional/2019/01/28/actualidad/1548699378_893143.html |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=[[El Pa\u00eds]] |date=29 January 2019 |language=es |quote=A diferencia de los siete anteriores, su construcci\u00f3n no se llev\u00f3 a cabo en los astilleros de San Fernando (C\u00e1diz), sino en los de Puerto Cabello, en el Estado de Carabobo (Venezuela)}}</ref> based on a standard Navantia Avante 1400 design.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.navantia.es/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Avante-1400.pdf|title=Wayback Machine|date=April 3, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200403021835/https://www.navantia.es/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Avante-1400.pdf|archive-date=2020-04-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.janes.com/article/95271/venezuelan-coast-guard-patrol-ship-sinks-following-collision|title=Venezuelan Coast Guard patrol ship sinks following collision &#124; Jane's 360|date=3 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200403023806/https://www.janes.com/article/95271/venezuelan-coast-guard-patrol-ship-sinks-following-collision|archive-date=3 April 2020}}</ref> The [[keel]] was [[Keel laying|laid]] in October 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.mnve.mil.ve/web/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=99&Itemid=31|title =Puesta de quilla del Tercer Buque de Vigilancia Litoral| accessdate =25 June 2009|publisher =Misi\u00f3n Naval Venezolana en Espa\u00f1a|date =October 2008|language =es|doi =|archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20090322172714/http://www.mnve.mil.ve/web/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=99&Itemid=31|archive-date =22 March 2009}}</ref>  The ship was [[Ceremonial ship launching|launched]] on 24 June 2009, christened by Alma Pura de Padr\u00f3n<ref>{{cite news |title=Navantia sigue entregando unidades navales para la Marina de Venezuela |url=https://andaluciainformacion.es/andalucia/63596/navantia-sigue-entregando-unidades-navales-para-la-marina-de-venezuela/#! |access-date=4 April 2020 |work=Andaluc\u00eda Informaci\u00f3n |date=24 June 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404101148/https://andaluciainformacion.es/andalucia/63596/navantia-sigue-entregando-unidades-navales-para-la-marina-de-venezuela/ |archivedate=4 April 2020 |language=es |quote=Alma Pura de Padr\u00f3n, madrina del acto, se mostr\u00f3 emocionada tras la botadura y cuando las sirenas de los remolcadores y del astillero isle\u00f1o sonaban por el acontecimiento}}</ref> and named after the city of [[Naiguat\u00e1]].  The [[Venezuelan Navy]] took delivery of ''Naiguat\u00e1'' from the builder and subsequently transferred it to the [[Venezuelan Coast Guard]]. Its weapons systems consisted of one Leonardo [[OTO Melara 76 mm]] gun, one [[Close-in weapon system|CIWS]] anti-aircraft/anti-missile [[Rheinmetall Oerlikon Millennium Gun]], and two 12.7 mm machine guns.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.infodefensa.com/latam/2020/02/26/noticia-chavez-sometido-quinta-prueba.html|archiveurl=http://archive.today/20200403025258/https://www.infodefensa.com/latam/2020/02/26/noticia-chavez-sometido-quinta-prueba.html|archive-date=3 April 2020 |url-status=dead|title=El BVL Hugo Ch\u00e1vez fue sometido a su quinta prueba de mar - Noticias Infodefensa Am\u00e9rica}}</ref>\n\n===Sinking===\n''Naiguat\u00e1'' sank following its purposeful ramming of the cruise liner {{ship||RCGS Resolute}} while in international waters on 30 March 2020.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/venezuelan-navy-ship-sinks-after-ramming-reinforced-cruise-liner-6t9wggf5d|title=Venezuelan navy ship sinks after ramming reinforced cruise liner|first=Stephen Gibbs|last=Venezuela|via=www.thetimes.co.uk}}</ref>  According to ''RCGS Resolute''{{'}}s owner, the Coast Guard ship had ordered the cruise ship to follow it to [[Isla Margarita]], a Venezuelan harbour.<ref>{{cite news |last1=K\u00e9vin STORME |title=Un navire de croisi\u00e8re coule un patrouilleur du V\u00e9n\u00e9zuela |url=https://lemarin.ouest-france.fr/secteurs-activites/defense/36360-venezuela-un-navire-de-croisiere-coule-un-patrouilleur |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=Le Marin |date=3 April 2020 |archiveurl=http://archive.is/UPbdf |archivedate=4 April 2020 |language=fr |quote=According to CCS, the patrol ship contacted RCGS Resolute before ordering him to follow him to Margarita Island.}}</ref>  ''Naiguat\u00e1'' sank with ''RCGS Resolute'' informing the international Maritime Rescue Coordination Centre (MRCC) of the incident offering assistance. After one hour staying in the area ''RCGS Resolute'' was informed through MRCC that assistance was not required as ''Naiguat\u00e1''{{'}}s crew had been rescued by the Venezuelan Navy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Kriegsschiff rammt Passagierschiff und sinkt |url=https://www.bild.de/politik/ausland/politik-ausland/kriegsschiff-rammt-deutsches-passagierschiff-und-sinkt-selbst-69805216.bild.html | accessdate=2 April 2020 |work=[[Bild]] |language=de }}</ref> \n\nThe [[President of Venezuela]] accused the captain of the cruise ship of \"[[piracy]]\" and \"[[terrorism]],\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/04/02/venezuelan-naval-vessel-goes-confrontation-portuguese-cruise/|title=Venezuelan naval vessel goes down after confrontation with Portuguese cruise ship|first=James|last=Badcock|newspaper=The Telegraph|date=April 2, 2020|via=www.telegraph.co.uk}}</ref> adding later that he did not rule out that ''RCGS Resolute'' was \"carrying mercenaries to attack onshore military bases.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.curacaochronicle.com/post/main/venezuelan-president-ship-that-is-docked-in-curacao-carries-mercenaries-to-attack-venezuela/|title=Venezuelan President: Ship that is docked in Cura\u00e7ao carries mercenaries to attack Venezuela|website=www.curacaochronicle.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nieuwsbladtransport.nl/scheepvaart/2020/04/02/venezolaans-marineschip-naar-de-kelder-na-rammen-pool-cruiseschip/|title=Venezolaans marineschip naar de kelder na rammen pool-cruiseschip|website=Nieuwsblad Transport}}</ref> The [[Ministry of Defense (Venezuela)|Venezuelan minister of defence]] said ''RCGS Resolute''{{'}}s action was an act of \"imperial aggression.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedrive.com/the-war-zone/32853/this-venezuelan-patrol-ship-sunk-itself-after-ramming-a-cruise-liner-with-an-reinforced-hull|title=This Venezuelan Patrol Ship Sunk Itself After Ramming A Cruise Liner With A Reinforced Hull|first=Joseph|last=Trevithick|website=The Drive}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n <!-- non-breaking space to keep AWB drones from altering the space before the navbox-->\n\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:Venezuelan patrol boat ''Naiguat\u00e1''|noerror}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Naiguat\u00e1}}\n[[Category:Patrol vessels]]\n[[Category:Ships of the Bolivarian Navy of Venezuela]]\n[[Category:2009 ships]]\n[[Category:Maritime incidents in 2020]]\n[[Category:Ships sunk in collisions]]\n[[Category:Shipwrecks in the Caribbean Sea]]\n", "text_old": "\n\n{{short description|Venezuelan coast guard boat}}\n{|{{Infobox ship begin}}\n{{Infobox ship image\n|Ship image=Arbv GC23.jpg\n|Ship caption=''Naiguat\u00e1'' during sea trials\n}}\n{{Infobox ship career\n|Hide header=\n|Ship country=Venezuela\n|Ship flag={{shipboxflag|Venezuela|naval}}\n|Ship name= ''Naiguat\u00e1''\n|Ship namesake= City of [[Naiguat\u00e1]]\n|Ship builder= [[Navantia]], [[C\u00e1diz]], Spain  \n|Ship laid down= October 2008\n|Ship launched= 24 June 2009\n|Ship commissioned= \n|Ship sponsor= Alma Pura de Padr\u00f3n\n|Ship identification = GC-23\n|Ship motto=\n|Ship fate=\n|Ship status= Sunk, 30 March 2020\n|Ship notes=           \n|Ship badge=\n}}\n{{Infobox ship characteristics\n| Hide header = \n| Header caption = \n| Ship class = {{sclass-|Guaicamacuto|patrol boat}}\n| Ship type =\n| Ship displacement =* {{cvt|1453|LT|0|lk=on}} (standard)\n* {{cvt|1720|LT|}} (full load)\n| Ship length = {{cvt|79.9|m|ftin}}\n| Ship beam = {{cvt|11.8|m|ftin}} (max.)<ref name=\"Navantia Avante 1400 patrol ship\">{{cite web|title=Navantia Avante 1400 patrol ship|url=http://www.navantia.es/ckfinder/userfiles/files/BVL(1).pdf|publisher=Navantia|accessdate=13 July 2013}}</ref>\n| Ship draught = {{cvt|7|m|ftin}}\n| Ship power =* 4 \u00d7 [[MTU Friedrichshafen|MTU]] 12V-1163-TB93\n* {{cvt|4440|kW|shp}}\n| Ship propulsion = *[[Combined diesel and diesel|CODAD]]\n*2 \u00d7 shaft with [[W\u00e4rtsil\u00e4]] 5C09 CP propeller<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wartsila.com/Wartsila/global/docs/en/ship_power/segments/navy/propulsion-solutions-for-OPVs.pdf|title=Wartsila Propulsion Solutions for OPVs}}</ref>\n| Ship speed = {{cvt|22|kn|lk=on}}\n| Ship range = {{cvt|4000|nmi|lk=in}} at {{cvt|16|kn}}\n| Ship complement = 34 + 30\n| Ship sensors = *'''Surface Search radar:''' Thales VARIANT, I - G band\n*'''Fire Control radar:''' Thales STING EO, I - K band with TV/IR/Laser\n*'''Electro-Optics:''' Thales MIRADOR\n| Ship armament = *1 \u00d7 [[Oto Melara 76 mm|{{cvt|76|mm}}/62 caliber Oto Melara gun]] (A position)\n*1 \u00d7 [[Rheinmetall Oerlikon Millennium Gun|{{cvt|35|mm}} Oerlikon Millennium gun]] (Y position)\n*2 \u00d7 {{cvt|12.7|mm}} guns (B position)\n| Ship armour = \n| Ship armor = \n| Ship aircraft = 1 \u00d7 [[Bell 212|AB212]], [[Bell 412|AB412]], or [[Eurocopter AS565 Panther|AS565]]\n| Ship aircraft facilities = Landing pad<ref name=\"Navantia Avante 1400 patrol ship\">{{cite web|title=Navantia Avante 1400 patrol ship|url=http://www.navantia.es/ckfinder/userfiles/files/BVL(1).pdf|publisher=Navantia|accessdate=13 July 2013}}</ref>\n| Ship notes = \n}}\n|}\n\n'''''Naiguat\u00e1''(GC-23)''', was a {{convert|79.9|m|adj=on}} littoral [[patrol boat]] of the Venezuelan Coast Guard.  The vessel was constructed by [[Navantia]] in [[C\u00e1diz]], Spain beginning in 2008. On 30 March 2020, the vessel rammed the [[cruise ship]] {{ship||RCGS Resolute}} in international waters and sank. \n\n==Construction and career==\n''Naiguat\u00e1'' was the third ship of the {{sclass-|Guaicamacuto|patrol boat|0}} BVLs.  BVL stands for \"Buque de Vigilancia de Litoral,\" which is Spanish for littoral [[Patrol boat|surveillance ship]].  It had a [[Displacement (ship)|displacement]] of 1,720 tons.<ref>{{cite news |last1= Lagneau |first=Laurent |title=Un patrouilleur de la marine v\u00e9n\u00e9zu\u00e9lienne a coul\u00e9 apr\u00e8s avoir percut\u00e9 un navire de croisi\u00e8re |url=http://www.opex360.com/2020/04/02/un-patrouilleur-de-la-marine-venezuelienne-a-coule-apres-avoir-percute-un-navire-de-croisiere/ |access-date=4 April 2020 |work=opex360 |date=2 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404093306/http://www.opex360.com/2020/04/02/un-patrouilleur-de-la-marine-venezuelienne-a-coule-apres-avoir-percute-un-navire-de-croisiere/ |archive-date=4 April 2020 |language=fr |quote=affichant 1.720 tonnes}}</ref>  It was built by Navantia in Spain at the [[San Fernando, C\u00e1diz|San Fernando]] shipyards in C\u00e1diz,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gonz\u00e1lez |first1=Miguel |title=Espa\u00f1a retira su apoyo al buque de guerra 'Comandante Eterno Hugo Ch\u00e1vez' |url=https://elpais.com/internacional/2019/01/28/actualidad/1548699378_893143.html |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=[[El Pa\u00eds]] |date=29 January 2019 |language=es |quote=A diferencia de los siete anteriores, su construcci\u00f3n no se llev\u00f3 a cabo en los astilleros de San Fernando (C\u00e1diz), sino en los de Puerto Cabello, en el Estado de Carabobo (Venezuela)}}</ref> based on a standard Navantia Avante 1400 design.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.navantia.es/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Avante-1400.pdf|title=Wayback Machine|date=April 3, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200403021835/https://www.navantia.es/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Avante-1400.pdf|archive-date=2020-04-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.janes.com/article/95271/venezuelan-coast-guard-patrol-ship-sinks-following-collision|title=Venezuelan Coast Guard patrol ship sinks following collision &#124; Jane's 360|date=3 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200403023806/https://www.janes.com/article/95271/venezuelan-coast-guard-patrol-ship-sinks-following-collision|archive-date=3 April 2020}}</ref> The [[keel]] was [[Keel laying|laid]] in October 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.mnve.mil.ve/web/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=99&Itemid=31|title =Puesta de quilla del Tercer Buque de Vigilancia Litoral| accessdate =25 June 2009|publisher =Misi\u00f3n Naval Venezolana en Espa\u00f1a|date =October 2008|language =es|doi =|archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20090322172714/http://www.mnve.mil.ve/web/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=99&Itemid=31|archive-date =22 March 2009}}</ref>  The ship was [[Ceremonial ship launching|launched]] on 24 June 2009, christened by Alma Pura de Padr\u00f3n<ref>{{cite news |title=Navantia sigue entregando unidades navales para la Marina de Venezuela |url=https://andaluciainformacion.es/andalucia/63596/navantia-sigue-entregando-unidades-navales-para-la-marina-de-venezuela/#! |access-date=4 April 2020 |work=Andaluc\u00eda Informaci\u00f3n |date=24 June 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404101148/https://andaluciainformacion.es/andalucia/63596/navantia-sigue-entregando-unidades-navales-para-la-marina-de-venezuela/ |archivedate=4 April 2020 |language=es |quote=Alma Pura de Padr\u00f3n, madrina del acto, se mostr\u00f3 emocionada tras la botadura y cuando las sirenas de los remolcadores y del astillero isle\u00f1o sonaban por el acontecimiento}}</ref> and named after the city of [[Naiguat\u00e1]].  The [[Venezuelan Navy]] took delivery of ''Naiguat\u00e1'' from the builder and subsequently transferred it to the [[Venezuelan Coast Guard]]. Its weapons systems consisted of one Leonardo [[OTO Melara 76 mm]] gun, one [[Close-in weapon system|CIWS]] anti-aircraft/anti-missile [[Rheinmetall Oerlikon Millennium Gun]], and two 12.7 mm machine guns.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.infodefensa.com/latam/2020/02/26/noticia-chavez-sometido-quinta-prueba.html|archiveurl=http://archive.today/20200403025258/https://www.infodefensa.com/latam/2020/02/26/noticia-chavez-sometido-quinta-prueba.html|archive-date=3 April 2020 |url-status=dead|title=El BVL Hugo Ch\u00e1vez fue sometido a su quinta prueba de mar - Noticias Infodefensa Am\u00e9rica}}</ref>\n\n===Sinking===\n''Naiguat\u00e1'' sank following its purposeful ramming of the cruise liner {{ship||RCGS Resolute}} while in international waters on 30 March 2020.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/venezuelan-navy-ship-sinks-after-ramming-reinforced-cruise-liner-6t9wggf5d|title=Venezuelan navy ship sinks after ramming reinforced cruise liner|first=Stephen Gibbs|last=Venezuela|via=www.thetimes.co.uk}}</ref>  According to ''RCGS Resolute''{{'}}s owner, the Coast Guard ship had ordered the cruise ship to follow it to [[Isla Margarita]], a Venezuelan harbour.<ref>{{cite news |last1=K\u00e9vin STORME |title=Un navire de croisi\u00e8re coule un patrouilleur du V\u00e9n\u00e9zuela |url=https://lemarin.ouest-france.fr/secteurs-activites/defense/36360-venezuela-un-navire-de-croisiere-coule-un-patrouilleur |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=Le Marin |date=3 April 2020 |archiveurl=http://archive.is/UPbdf |archivedate=4 April 2020 |language=fr |quote=According to CCS, the patrol ship contacted RCGS Resolute before ordering him to follow him to Margarita Island.}}</ref>  ''Naiguat\u00e1'' sank with ''RCGS Resolute'' informing the international Maritime Rescue Coordination Centre (MRCC) of the incident offering assistance. After one hour staying in the area ''RCGS Resolute'' was informed through MRCC that assistance was not required as ''Naiguat\u00e1''{{'}}s crew had been rescued by the Venezuelan Navy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Kriegsschiff rammt Passagierschiff und sinkt |url=https://www.bild.de/politik/ausland/politik-ausland/kriegsschiff-rammt-deutsches-passagierschiff-und-sinkt-selbst-69805216.bild.html | accessdate=2 April 2020 |work=[[Bild]] |language=de }}</ref> \n\nThe [[President of Venezuela]] accused the captain of the cruise ship of \"[[piracy]]\" and \"[[terrorism]],\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/04/02/venezuelan-naval-vessel-goes-confrontation-portuguese-cruise/|title=Venezuelan naval vessel goes down after confrontation with Portuguese cruise ship|first=James|last=Badcock|newspaper=The Telegraph|date=April 2, 2020|via=www.telegraph.co.uk}}</ref> adding later that he did not rule out that ''RCGS Resolute'' was \"carrying mercenaries to attack onshore military bases.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.curacaochronicle.com/post/main/venezuelan-president-ship-that-is-docked-in-curacao-carries-mercenaries-to-attack-venezuela/|title=Venezuelan President: Ship that is docked in Cura\u00e7ao carries mercenaries to attack Venezuela|website=www.curacaochronicle.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nieuwsbladtransport.nl/scheepvaart/2020/04/02/venezolaans-marineschip-naar-de-kelder-na-rammen-pool-cruiseschip/|title=Venezolaans marineschip naar de kelder na rammen pool-cruiseschip|website=Nieuwsblad Transport}}</ref> The [[Ministry of Defense (Venezuela)|Venezuelan minister of defence]] said ''RCGS Resolute''{{'}}s action was an act of \"imperial aggression.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedrive.com/the-war-zone/32853/this-venezuelan-patrol-ship-sunk-itself-after-ramming-a-cruise-liner-with-an-reinforced-hull|title=This Venezuelan Patrol Ship Sunk Itself After Ramming A Cruise Liner With A Reinforced Hull|first=Joseph|last=Trevithick|website=The Drive}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n <!-- non-breaking space to keep AWB drones from altering the space before the navbox-->\n\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:Venezuelan patrol boat ''Naiguat\u00e1''|noerror}}\n